# Device Deployment Safety

## NEVER uninstall a previous version before installing

When installing or deploying the app on any device (physical or emulator), **never uninstall the existing version first**. User data (books, reading progress, settings) lives on the device and is wiped by an uninstall.

Always use commands that perform an **in-place update** (install over the existing APK):

```bash
# ✅ GOOD — updates in place, preserves user data
flutter build apk --debug
adb -s <device_id> install -r build/app/outputs/flutter-apk/app-debug.apk

# ❌ BAD — flutter install uninstalls first, destroying user data
flutter install -d <device_id> --debug
```

The `-r` flag in `adb install -r` means "replace existing application" and does **not** wipe data.

## Only uninstall when explicitly instructed

Only run `adb uninstall`, `flutter install` (which uninstalls first), or any command that removes the app if the user **explicitly asks** to wipe/delete the previous version.
